Required packages
=================

These package names are for building raveloxmidi from source. Package
names may vary slightly between distribution releases.

Ubuntu/Debian
-------------

Build from source:

autoconf
automake
build-essential
libasound2-dev
libavahi-client-dev
libtool
pkg-config

Memory leak checks:

valgrind

Build .deb packages:

dpkg-dev

Runtime:

avahi-daemon
libavahi-client3
libasound2

Fedora/Red Hat
--------------

Build from source:

alsa-lib-devel
autoconf
automake
avahi-devel
gcc
libtool
make
pkgconf-pkg-config

Memory leak checks:

valgrind

Build .rpm packages:

diffutils
findutils
gzip
rpm-build
sed
tar

Runtime:

alsa-lib
avahi
avahi-libs

Docker validation
-----------------

The Docker package and memcheck validation targets require Docker and
Docker Compose on the host. The container images install their own
distro-specific build dependencies.

Notes
-----

Avahi must be running at runtime for raveloxmidi to register its
zeroconf service name.

ALSA support is optional at configure time. If the ALSA development
package is missing, the build continues without rawmidi support.
